A rise in sadistic murders and attacks on children accused of witchcraft by their families and loved-ones means police will now receive specialist training.

The Met has admitted its officers are rarely able to spot the signs that a youngster is in danger despite dealing with 81 sorcery cases in the last decade.

Its religious violence unit will now offer all staff training in a pilot scheme that could be rolled out across the country after a spate of high profile cases.

